Package: tgif
Version: 4.1.44
Revision: 1
GCC: 3.3
BuildDepends: x11-dev, gettext-bin, gettext-dev
Depends: app-defaults, netpbm-bin, x11-shlibs, gettext, rman
Source: ftp://bourbon.usc.edu/pub/tgif/%n-QPL-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 4818d79d36c460e24d14a390ade371e9
PatchScript: <<
 sed 's|@PREFIX@|%p|g'  <%a/%n.patch | patch -p1
 cp Tgif.tmpl-darwin Tgif.tmpl
<<
CompileScript: <<
 xmkmf
 make tgif
 cd po; xmkmf ; make Makefile Makefiles depend all
<<
InstallScript: <<
 make DESTDIR=%d BINDIR=%p/bin TGIFDIR=%p/share/%n \
      MANDIR=%p/share/man/man1 DOCDIR=%p/share/doc/%n install install.man
 install -m 755 -d             %i/etc/app-defaults
 install -m 755 tgif.Xdefaults %i/etc/app-defaults/Tgif
 cd po; make NLSDIR=%i/share/locale install
<<
DocFiles: Copyright HISTORY LICENSE.QPL README rmcast/README.tgwb
ConfFiles: %p/etc/app-defaults/Tgif
Description: Xlib base 2-D drawing facility under X11
DescDetail: <<
What is tgif?
 - Tgif (pronounced t-g-i-f) is an Xlib based interactive 2-D
   drawing tool under X11 on Linux and most UNIX platforms.

 - Tgif becomes a hyper-structured-graphics (or hyper-graphics)
   editor/browser on the World-Wide-Web in version 2.16 
   (released on Dec 3, 1994).
Do tgif http://bourbon.usc.edu:8001/tgif/index.obj
        to see the tgif hyper-graphics home page.
<<
